<div class="collection-template collection-template-default">
  <div class="container">
    {% render 'breadcrumb' %}

    <div class="halo-collection-content">
      <div class="row">
        {% render 'sidebar-filter' %}
        {% render 'collection-template-default' %}
      </div>

      {% if collection.handle == 'single-axles' %}
        <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Why Choose a Single Axle Trailer?</div>

          <p>
            Single axle trailers are a popular choice for everyday transport needs because they are lighter, easier to manoeuvre and more economical to tow. They are ideal for garden waste, landscaping equipment, ride-on mowers, tools, building supplies and general household use.
          </p>

          <p>
            Whether you need a trailer for weekend projects or regular business use, a single axle trailer provides a practical and dependable solution without the additional weight and complexity of a tandem axle model.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Why Choose X-Trailers?</div>

          <p>
            At X-Trailers, we build trailers for real New Zealand conditions. Our trailers are manufactured using hot-dip galvanised steel to provide long-term protection against rust and corrosion. Designed for durability and reliability, our trailers are trusted by homeowners, contractors, landscapers and rural property owners throughout New Zealand.
          </p>

          <p>
            With a range of sizes and configurations available, our team can help you find the right trailer for your specific needs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Visit Our Auckland Showroom</div>

          <p>
            Want to see our trailers in person? Visit X-Trailers at 6C Rennie Drive, Māngere, Auckland, where you can view our range of trailers and speak with our team about the best option for your requirements. We also offer nationwide delivery throughout New Zealand.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="collection-faq-section">

      <div class="seo-section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</div>

      <details class="collection-faq-item" open>
        <summary>What size single axle trailer should I choose?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>For general household and garden use, smaller trailer sizes are often sufficient. For landscaping, ride-on mowers or trade work, larger trailer sizes may provide additional capacity and flexibility.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need brakes on a single axle trailer?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Brake requirements depend on the trailer's weight and intended use. If you are unsure which option is suitable, our team can help you choose the correct trailer.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I tow a single axle trailer with a standard vehicle?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Many single axle trailers can be towed by standard vehicles, however towing capacity varies between vehicles. Always check your vehicle manufacturer's towing specifications.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>What warranty do X-Trailers trailers come with?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>X-Trailers trailers are backed by a 5-year warranty on the trailer frame and a 1-year warranty on trailer parts.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Do you offer trailer finance?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Finance options are available on selected trailer models. Contact our team for current finance options and eligibility requirements.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    {% elsif collection.handle == 'tandem-axles' %}
      <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Built Tough for Big Loads</div>

          <p>
            When the job demands more, a tandem axle trailer gets it done. Designed for heavier loads, improved stability and smoother towing, tandem axle trailers are a popular choice for commercial operators, contractors, farmers and machinery transport.
          </p>

          <p>
            Their dual axle design helps distribute weight more effectively, providing better balance and greater control when towing on New Zealand roads.
           </p> 
        </div>
        
        <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Why Choose X-Trailers?</div>

          <p>
            At X-Trailers, we know what it takes to handle real Kiwi conditions because we build trailers for them. Whether you are hauling machinery to a worksite, transporting equipment around the farm, or moving heavy materials, our tandem axle trailers are built to perform.
          </p>

          <p>
            Constructed using hot-dip galvanised steel for long-lasting rust protection and durability, our trailers are designed to deliver reliable performance in demanding environments.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="custom-collection-bottom-content">
          <div class="seo-section-title">Visit Our Auckland Showroom</div>

          <p>
            Visit X-Trailers at 6C Rennie Drive, Māngere, Auckland to compare trailer options in person. Our team can help you select the right tandem axle trailer for your specific requirements. Nationwide delivery is available throughout New Zealand.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="collection-faq-section">

      <div class="seo-section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</div>

      <details class="collection-faq-item" open>
        <summary>What is the 60/40 rule for trailer axles?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>The 60/40 rule is a loading guideline where approximately 60% of the trailer weight is positioned in front of the axle group and 40% behind it. This helps improve balance and towing stability.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>What is the difference between a tandem trailer and a box trailer?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>A box trailer describes the trailer body style, while tandem axle refers to the trailer having two axles. A box trailer can be either single axle or tandem axle.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Are tandem trailers better for long-distance towing?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Tandem axle trailers generally offer improved stability and smoother towing, making them well suited for longer journeys and heavier loads.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I use a tandem axle trailer for landscaping jobs?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Tandem axle trailers are commonly used for transporting landscaping equipment, ride-on mowers, materials and machinery</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>What is the best tandem trailer for moving large equipment?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>The best trailer depends on the size and weight of the equipment being transported. Our team can help recommend the most suitable model for your requirements.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>What warranty do X-Trailers trailers come with?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>X-Trailers trailers are backed by a 5-year warranty on the trailer frame and a 1-year warranty on trailer parts.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="collection-faq-item">
        <summary>Do you offer trailer finance?</summary>
        <div class="collection-faq-answer">
          <p>Finance options are available on selected trailer models. Contact our team for current finance options and eligibility requirements.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

  {% endif %}

    </div>   
  </div>
</div>